== English ==
=== Verb with Conjunction ===
''to'' '''go after''' ''something happens''
# To [[go]] following an event.
#: ''You can '''go after''' the light turns green.''
#: ''Nobody wanted to leave, but they all '''went after''' the cops arrived.''
#: ''This opponent may still not have '''gone after''' the sun has set.''

=== Verb with Preposition ===
''to'' '''go after''' ''something''
# To [[go]] following an event.
#: ''The bank is closed today, but our boss usually '''goes after''' lunch.''

=== Verb with Preposition ===
''to'' '''go after''' ''someone''
# To be the next to [[go]].
#: ''That man was here first. You can '''go after''' him.''

=== Phrasal Verb ===
''to'' '''go after''' ''something''
# To [[pursue]] an object or a goal.
#: ''In little league, usually everyone '''goes after''' the ball.''
#: ''Inspired, the scientist '''went''' right '''after''' the new idea.''
''to'' '''go after''' ''someone''
# To pursue in attempt to [[catch]] another.
#: ''The downed officer couldn't '''go after''' the criminal.''

